Power Analysis

2021-06-08

Presented here is the power analysis for the target and cohort fits on each condition. Included are the bootstrapped curves from bdots, the power curve functions assuming an effect size equal to 80%, 100%, and 120% of what was observed. Finally, a table indicating average effect size and number of subjects needed for 80% power, assuming the observed effect size.

  1. This is on the unjacknifed fits

  2. Assumes conservative estimate of dropping 10% of subjects due to poor fits in either target or cohort (actual percentage dropped was 8%)

  3. Effect size is determined as average \(t\)-statistic in 100ms window of maximum

Target Power Calculations

Subjects needed to observe 100% effect size:

Average Effect Size N for 80% Power
ExpectNoise vs NoiseBoth 1.78381 6
ExpectNoise vs Quiet 0.60787 48
NoiseBoth vs Quiet 1.74646 6
